"<div class=\"modal route-details sailingAvailabilityModal\" id=\"y_ccSailingAvailabilityDetails\" role=\"dialog\" >\n    <div class=\"modal-dialog\" role=\"document\">\n        <div class=\"modal-content\">\n            <div class=\"modal-header pb-0\">\n                <h6 class=\"text-dark-blue\">Vancouver (Horseshoe Bay)<p style=\"display:inline;border-bottom:none;\"> to</p> Sunshine Coast (Langdale)</h6>\n                <a class=\"modal-close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\">\n                    <span class=\"bcf bcf-icon-close\"></span>\n                </a>\n            </div>\n\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\n                <p class=\"fnt-14 font-italic text-dark-blue\" style=\"border-bottom: none;\">\n                    </p>\n                <p>\n                    Vehicle space availability shows an estimate of how much remaining vehicle space is available for a sailing. This estimate doesn't include vehicles outside the terminal waiting to buy a ticket.</p>\n                <h5 class=\"departure-label\">\n                    Departure</h5>\n                <p class=\"modal-time\">\n                    <span class=\"clock\">2:23<span>pm</span></span>\n                              <span class=\"sailing-duration\">Sailing duration:&nbsp;0h 40m</span>\n\n                    <span class=\"arrival-location\">Queen of Coquitlam</span>\n                </p>\n\n                <h5 class=\"estimated-space\">Estimated vehicle space available</h5>\n                <div class=\"standard-vehicle-space clearfix\">\n                    <p class=\"vehicle-icon-text cc-percent-modal-vehicle-align\">\n                            <span class=\"percentage\">20%</span>\n                                </p>\n                        <div>\n                            <p class=\"font-weight-bold text-dark-blue vehicle-total-text\">Total vehicle space available</p>\n                            <p class=\"vehicle-total-text\">on the entire ferry</p>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                <div class=\"standard-vehicle-space clearfix\">\n                    <p class=\"vehicle-icon-text cc-percent-modal-vehicle-align\">\n                            <span class=\"bcf bcf-icon-std-car bcf-icon-sm cc-percent-modal-icon \" ></span>\n\n                            <span class=\"percentage\">  3% </span>\n                                </p>\n                        <div>\n                           <p class=\"font-weight-bold text-dark-blue std-car-text\">Under height vehicle deck</p>\n                           <p class=\"std-car-text\">Only vehicles 7 ft. (2.13 m) high and under (most cars, vans and SUVs).</p>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                <div class=\"mixed-vehicle-space clearfix\">\n                    <p class=\"vehicle-icon-text cc-percent-modal-vehicle-align\">\n                            <span class=\"cc-modal bcf bcf-icon-mixed-vehicle bcf-icon-sm cc-percent-modal-icon\"></span>\n                            <span class=\"percentage\">  64% </span>\n                                </p>\n                        <div>\n                           <p class=\"font-weight-bold text-dark-blue std-car-text\">Mixed vehicle deck</p>\n                           <p class=\"std-car-text\">Any vehicle height including those over 7 ft. (2.13 m) high, such as trucks, buses and RVs.</p>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                <p class=\"modal-extra-vehicle-info cc-text-grey\">For customer convenience, each vehicle deck has its own estimated percentage of available space. This is particularly important for those with over height vehicles, as they can only fit on the lower vehicle deck. The overall available space is a calculation of the space remaining on both decks as it relates to the entire ferry.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n"